This paper proposes a new reinforcement learning method for cooperative multi-agent systems. It is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves developing a new actor-critic method. It also involves multi-agent systems, which could lead to it being classified under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also mentions the coordination of autonomous vehicles, which could lead to it being classified under cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper involves the use of counterfactual baselines, which could lead to it being classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
